subject_information.comments: It was fun.  I was waiting for you to test my memory of what was moved behind a curtain.  Or to ask for an item to be moved from behind a curtain which I didn't know the identity of.  Thank you for not doing that!
subject_information.strategy: At first I figured the other player would only move the objects that weren't behind the curtains because they should have known that I didn't know they were there.  That didn't work every time so I began describing the objects in more detail.  Later, I shortened the commands to just item name and direction to speed things up.
